-- Ghana Rainfall Report for Cocoa Regions, Feb. 1-10
-- B y   M o s e s   M o z a r t   D z a w u
-- 2012-02-16T11:57:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-16/ghana-rainfall-report-for-cocoa-regions-feb-1-10-table-.html
The following are rainfall figures
for selected areas of  Ghana , the world’s second-biggest cocoa
producer, from Feb. 1 to Feb. 10, according to the Ghana
Meteorological Agency.  The Western region, which includes the towns of Sefwi
Bekwai and Bogoso, is Ghana’s largest growing area for the
chocolate ingredient, accounting for 55 percent of output,
according to the Ghana Cocoa Board.  The Ashanti region accounts for about 18 percent of
production, while Brong Ahafo generates 9.3 percent, the Eastern
region 8.6 percent and the Central region 8.8 percent. Volta
accounts for 0.1 percent, the board said.  Ivory Coast , which borders Ghana, is the world’s largest
cocoa producer.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Moses Mozart Dzawu in Accra at 
